  <h1>TDS on winnings: Section 194B and online gaming 194BA</h1>
  <div class="byline">
    <span class="av">SR</span><b>Written by a Chartered Accountant</b>
    <span class="sep"></span><span>NumberIQ Editorial</span>
    <span class="sep"></span><span>Last reviewed June 2026</span>
    <span class="sep"></span><span>5 min read</span>
  </div>
</header>
<div class="divide"></div>

<article class="prose read">
  <p class="answer-first lead"><b>TDS on winnings from lotteries, crossword puzzles, card games and game shows is deducted at 30% under Section 194B, and winnings from online games are deducted at 30% under Section 194BA on net winnings.</b> For online gaming there is no minimum threshold; winnings are taxed without any deduction or basic exemption.</p>

  <div class="toc"><b>On this page</b><a href="#s0">Section 194B (lotteries, game shows)</a> &middot; <a href="#s1">Section 194BA (online gaming)</a> &middot; <a href="#s2">Comparison</a> &middot; <a href="#s3">Practical points</a></div>

  <!-- ADSENSE SLOT 1 — activate after approval -->

  <h2 id="s0">Section 194B (lotteries, game shows)</h2>
<p>Winnings from <b>lotteries, crossword puzzles, card games, gambling, betting and game shows</b> are subject to TDS at <b>30%</b> under Section 194B where the amount exceeds Rs.10,000 (aggregate during the year). The income is taxed at a <b>flat 30%</b> under Section 115BB with no deductions, expenses or basic exemption.</p>

  <h2 id="s1">Section 194BA (online gaming)</h2>
<p>For <b>online games</b>, Section 194BA applies TDS at <b>30% on 'net winnings'</b> in the user's account, computed at withdrawal and at year-end. There is <b>no Rs.10,000 threshold</b> &mdash; all net winnings are covered. Net winnings broadly = withdrawals + closing balance &minus; deposits &minus; opening balance, per the prescribed formula.</p>

  <h2 id="s2">Comparison</h2>
<div class="table-wrap"><table><thead><tr><th>Feature</th><th>194B</th><th>194BA</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Covers</td><td>Lottery, game show, betting</td><td>Online games</td></tr><tr><td>Rate</td><td>30%</td><td>30%</td></tr><tr><td>Threshold</td><td>Rs.10,000</td><td>None</td></tr><tr><td>Base</td><td>Gross winnings</td><td>Net winnings (formula)</td></tr></tbody></table></div>

  <h2 id="s3">Practical points</h2>
<ul><li>Winnings in <b>kind</b> require the payer to ensure tax is paid before release (grossed up).</li><li>No basic exemption, deduction or set-off against these winnings.</li><li>Report the income and TDS via <a href="form-26as-ais-tis-difference.html">26AS/AIS</a>.</li><li>The flat 30% (plus cess) means effective tax of about 31.2%.</li></ul>

  <div class="faq">
    <h2 id="faq">Frequently asked questions</h2>
    <details><summary>What is the TDS rate on lottery or game-show winnings?</summary><p>30% under Section 194B where winnings exceed Rs.10,000; the income is taxed at a flat 30% with no deductions or basic exemption.</p></details>
    <details><summary>How is TDS on online gaming winnings calculated?</summary><p>At 30% on net winnings under Section 194BA, computed at each withdrawal and at year-end using the prescribed formula; there is no minimum threshold.</p></details>
    <details><summary>Can I claim expenses against gaming winnings?</summary><p>No. Winnings under Sections 194B/194BA are taxed at a flat 30% under Section 115BB with no deduction, expense or basic exemption allowed.</p></details>
  </div>

  <!-- ADSENSE SLOT 2 — activate after approval -->

  <div class="key-takeaways"><h2>Key takeaways</h2>
    <ul><li>194B: 30% on lottery/game-show winnings above Rs.10,000.</li><li>194BA: 30% on online-gaming net winnings, no threshold.</li><li>Flat 30% (about 31.2% with cess); no deductions or set-off.</li><li>Winnings in kind are grossed up before release.</li></ul>
  </div>

